.nr X
.if \nX=0 .ds x} reset 1F "Form and Menu Language Interpreter Utilities" "\&"
.if \nX=1 .ds x} reset 1F "Form and Menu Language Interpreter Utilities"
.if \nX=2 .ds x} reset 1F "" "\&"
.if \nX=3 .ds x} reset "" "" "\&"
.TH \*(x}
.SH NAME
\f4reset\f1 \- reset the current form field to its default values
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f4reset\f1
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f4reset\f1 function causes the \f4value\f1 descriptor of
the current field to be re-evaluated, restoring the default value of
the field if the current value is different.
The descriptor is re-evaluated even if it has been modified by \f4const\f1.
.ig
BUILT-IN FMLI
